text.tspan: Change in share of adults who are overweight or obese, 1975 to 2016
"Overweight" is defined here as having a body mass index (BMI) equal to or greater than 25. BMI is a person's
weight in kilograms divided by their height in meters squared.
Data source: WHO, Global Health Observatory
